  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nPrior to Vyper 0.3.0, Vyper did not always perform ABI encoding (and possibly decoding?) correctly.  The exact extent of this needs to be investigated, but, it would be good if Codec could detect when you're using a Vyper version prior to 0.3.0, and adjust its decoding (and possibly encoding?) accordingly.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.4.14",
